    "However, downstream constraints may only allow a pressure of 0-3 Bar.",
    "In such cases, a system-imposed limit is put in place.",
    "With respect to service provisioning boundaries, they are deduced from extensive knowledge and tests to determine the safe range for consumption.",
    "For example, a water treatment process must ensure that adding acid and/or base chemicals do not significantly result in the pH of water moving away from 7 (neutral).",
    "The OEM/system imposed limits for transport components and deduced limits for service provisioning parts are fed into one or more controllers, such as a PLC (see Fig. 1)."
